      • onDepthEntryAdd

        public boolean onDepthEntryAdd(IInstrument instrument,
                               boolean aggregated,
                               int entryID,
                               boolean buy,
                               int price,
                               int qty,
                               IMarketDataItem[] values)
        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentDepthListener
        Called when a particular depth entry has been added.

        IMPORTANT NOTE

        The values array is reused - so you should not store a reference to it. You should not process the full array. Processing of the array should terminate once an entry with a 0 fieldID is encountered.
        Specified by:
        onDepthEntryAdd in interface IInstrumentDepthListener
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument whose depth has changed.
        aggregated - True if aggregated depth, false if not (ie detail).
        entryID - ID of entry being added.
        buy - True if this is a buy side entry.
        price - Price level of this entry.
        qty - Quantity of entry.
        values - Other information associated with entry. May be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.

      • onDepthEntryChange

        public boolean onDepthEntryChange(IInstrument instrument,
                                  boolean aggregated,
                                  int entryID,
                                  boolean buy,
                                  int price,
                                  int qty,
                                  IUpdateEntry[] changes)
        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentDepthListener
        Called when a particular depth entry has changed or been deleted.

        Deleted depth entries cause this to be called with qty == 0.

        IMPORTANT NOTE

        The changes array is reused - so you should not store a reference to it. You should not process the full array. Processing of the array should terminate once an entry with a 0 fieldID is encountered.
        Specified by:
        onDepthEntryChange in interface IInstrumentDepthListener
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument whose depth has changed.
        aggregated - True if aggregated depth, false if not (ie detail).
        entryID - ID of entry being changed.
        buy - True if this is a buy side entry.
        price - Price level of this entry.
        qty - Quantity of entry.
        changes - Other information associated with entry. May be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.

      • onSubscriptionError

        public boolean onSubscriptionError(IInstrument instrument,
                                   String requestID,
                                   int errorCode,
                                   String sourceErrorCode,
                                   String sourceErrorMessage)
        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentMarketDataListener
        Called when the request to listen to updates on a particular instrument was rejected.

        Typically this will called in response to an asynchronous error response to a call to one of the addXXXListener methods on an IMarketDataStore. See the JavaDoc for those methods.

        Specified by:
        onSubscriptionError in interface IInstrumentMarketDataListener
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument associated with the subscription error.
        requestID - Request ID passed in the add listener method call which resulted in this error. May be null if no ID was specified on the call.
        errorCode - One of the standard IInstrument error values - IInstrument.SUBSCRIPTION_ERROR_UNKNOWN if the reason for the error is unknown.
        sourceErrorCode - Code supplied by the market data source indicating the nature of the error - may be null.
        sourceErrorMessage - String supplied by the market data source describing the nature of the error - may be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.

        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentTopOfBookListener

        Processing of the array of changes should terminate when the first entry with a fieldID <= 0 is encountered. The rest of the array should not be processed.
        Specified by:

        changes - Array of IUpdateEntry
        Returns:

      • release

        public void release(IMarketDataBufferEntry entry)
        Description copied from interface: IMarketDataBuffer
        The buffer should have the ability to reuse objects in order to reduce object creation.

        When a user has finished processing the entry return by a call to IMarketDataBuffer.get() they can call this method passing the entry so that it can be reused. This will reduce object creation and can increase performance.

        Specified by:
        release in interface IMarketDataBuffer
        Parameters:
        entry - Entry which can be reused.
